Virtual environment
A way to separate different python environment installation.

Create
The module venv is used to create a virtual environment, it usually creates a folder which contains Python interpreter, the standard library, and various supporting files
```
python -m venv VirtualName
```

Activate
A python interpreter installed in a venv cannot be realized by shell directly, if you want to use it as a default python, you can activate it
```
$ source ./venv/virtualname/activate
(virtuanlName) $ python -v
```

Pip package management
Search
pip search packageName

Add
pip install packageName
pip install packageName=version

Update
pip install packageName=version
pip upgrade packageName

Delete
pip uninstall packageName
